16/06/2004
ATHENS, Greece -- Prime Minister Costas Karamanlis announced on Tuesday (15 June) that the ruling New Democracy (ND) party will hold a national congress from 23 July to 25 July.
The congress will spell out ND's programme for development, aimed at securing better social protections and a higher standard of living.
Also Tuesday, Justice Minister Anastasis Papaligouras submitted a new draft law to parliament regarding the European arrest warrant and measures against terrorism.
Papaligouras said he hoped the law would bolster government efforts to guarantee the security of the Summer Olympics.
(The Guardian, AFP - 16/06/04;
ANA - 15/06/04)
